{
  "stem": "11133.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I think-- and the fear of not knowing where we were going-- you know, really, I mean, we didn't-- we were being-- the reason it took so long-- I mean, Krakow and Auschwitz are very close.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's only like 35 miles, or no more than 50 miles away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But because the Russians were approaching, there were many trains being shunted over to different sidelines-- styled rails, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's why it took-- it didn't take three days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It just took a day and a half, I think.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It took us three and a half days to go from Auschwitz to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was the long trip.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we ended up in Auschwitz in the middle of the night, and that was a horrible experience.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fear, smell, burning flesh, shouting, orders, not knowing which way to-- music being played.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Slush, on-- you know-- on-- the mud on the-- on the road.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, the Germans barking at us-- get out, get out, get out, you know, from the cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All the time.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was with my mother all the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, the first place they took us to, they walked us into the sauna, which is the-- supposedly the delousing room, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we, at that point, already had heard what happened in Auschwitz, so when they told us to strip and take our clothes off, and they shaved our heads and all that, and they shoved us into the-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the shower room, you know, we didn't know what to expect, you know?",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Whether we were going to have the gas, or whether we were going to have actual water.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they gave us clothes.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
